Yeah, same exact point in the essay posted above in someone else post (actually it's the same paragraph word for word.)  But, if the machines were programmed to serve, and can't override their programming, why did they turn on the humans in the first place?  Are we to assume they realized that humans, left to their own devices, would surely destroy themselves, so in the machines' logic, they needed to conquer and preserve the humans who would otherwise eventually commit genocide on themselves?  I don't buy it (But the more I think about it, the more this seems like a motive that the brother's Wachowski would use to start this war...)<br>
<br>
If the machines are programmed to serve, why did they start the whole &quot;let's kill and enslave humanity&quot; bit in the first place?  Clearly, if they are truly thinking machines, they can step outside of their programming, and follow what they deem is the logical choice.  Even moreso the generations of machine being built and programmed by machines.  The machines built by man might be programmed to serve, but the thinking machines being created later (by machines themselves) wouldn't have this programming.  You could argue that the inherent programming in the man-made machines would dictate that all subsequent generations to also be programmed with a subroutine telling them to serve man, but if the machines aren't able to even write that out of their software, how did they manage to break free of their programming to overthrow humanity in the first place?  If the AI that started this all was truly a thinking machine, self-aware and capable of learning, it should have the capability to realize errors in it's programming, and move beyond them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jaelyndimathe>Jaelyn DiMathe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guardian of Truth</span><br>  Posts: 497<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/22/03 2:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1566.topic&index=42>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://myweb.cableone.net/agunders/jae.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Yeeeeaah ...  8^p</span><hr size=1> Plus, we can assume that the machines are able to move beyond their programming, leadin