Me and a buddy were discussing the same question after the movie.  One of our theories was that the Matrix needed a &quot;reboot&quot; because Agent Smith was spreading like a virus.  However, doing so would kill all the humans connected to the Matrix.  Looking at it this way, Zion could be used by the machines as an alternate source for humans to repopulate the Matrix.  By keeping Zion going they ensure they have a back-up generator, so to speak.  This, in effect, mirroring the conversation between Neo and the councilman on the lower decks of Zion.<br>
