But would they even need it?  I'm not sure if the infants they are growing are attached to the matrix, but based on the first movie I don't think they are.  They show the fields where the babies are growing/harvested, and then a seperate scene where an infant is put in one of the pods and plugged into the system.  This seems to me that the infant isn't hooked in at all until that point, and really they wouldn't need to be (not like there's alot of stimulation in the womb in real-life, just a dull roar.)  So, if the growing babies aren't plugged in, they shouldn't be lost if the system crashes.  It would also make sense to not have them plugged in until absolutely necessary for that reason as well...if something goes wrong, you don't lose everything.  Again, leaving no use for the machines to leave Zion alone if they could truly destroy it as easily as the Architect would have Neo believe.<br>
